rComments: Best Professor I ever had, enthusiastic and truly loves what she does.

Naomi has a real knack for boiling things down to simple, intuitive concepts, and she's fun and approachable to boot.  Her teaching style meshes especially well with honors students and Physics majors.

SUCH a nice professor, and sooo enthusiastic! She really loves what she teaches, and still gets excited. The subject itself was interesting, but pretty hard for me. However, if you go to office hours, she'll help you through every, single homework problem, if needed, and that allows you to easily get an A. Take 199 HM!!!

She's easily the best professor I've had at this university. Tough concepts I was struggling with even before this class now make sense to me. She really knows what she's doing and she's hilarious on top of that so it's a ton of fun to go to class. Plus if you go to office hours she'll work with you until you figure out the problems.
She is a really enthusiastic teacher and really care about students.

Naomi was probably the best and most enthusiastic professor I will ever have. I ditched my professors afternoon lectures to go to hers in the morning. She made the material very understandable and put online lots of key notes that basically gave away how to do any problem on the exam.
Excellent teacher!  made E&M fun and accessible

Naomi was a very enthusiastic and decent prof. Focused more on actually teaching than reading from the Powerpoint. Did a lot of problem working on the board. Make sure to go to class and don't sit in back—there's no magnified projection of the board.  Go to class and office hours and you'll be fine. WARNING: YOU WILL HATE GAUSSÂ’S LAW.
She is a particularly good lecturer and very helpful.  I had 8:30 lecture with her, and it was good.
She is the best professor I have had to UIUC in my 3 semesters here. she made me want to go to class, and she was a very able and enthusiatic lecturer
this is your chance to learn E&M! don't waste it! she is awesome!
Very dedicated professor. She knows what she's talking about and she did her best to make very boring material at least somewhat interesting.

She makes physics very interesting. I have an 8am class and thanks to her, I wouldn't miss a single lecture. She only uses her power point slides to supplement her lecture and all the important details is written on the board. Make sure you practise exam type problems. Lectures will only help students understand the concepts. Highly recommended!
Lectures don't help students learn, even if you do read the book.
yea this teacher is awesome, I strongly recommend her. The class itself isn't bad, just do practice tests and you'll do fine.
This prof. is the coolest physics prof. I've ever met.
